The government would permit panchayats to expend their Plan funds for popularising the cultivation of medicinal plants and also creating a public awareness of the need for conserving traditional medicines, Minister of Panchayats M.K. Muneer has said. He was inaugurating a meet of traditional healers here on Thursday. District panchayat president V.K. Madhu was the chief guest. Kerala Institute of Local Administration (KILA) Director P.P. Balan, who addressed the meet, said that local bodies should formulate schemes for biodiversity conservation. Kerala Grama Panchayat Association president P.T. Mathew presided. â€” Special Correspondent